%N A395953 Decimal expansion of the expected distance from the center of a unit disk to a line that passes through two points independently and uniformly selected at random in the disk.
%C A395953 The mean of the probability distributed function f(x) = (16/(3*Pi))*(1-x^2)^(3/2) for 0 <= x <= 1, and 0 otherwise.
%D A395953 A. M. Mathai, An Introduction to Geometrical Probability: Distributional Aspects with Applications, Amsterdam: Gordon and Breach, 1999, p. 205, eq. (2.3.66).
%H A395953 F. Garwood and E. M. Holroyd, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/3614676">The Distance of a "Random Chord" of a Circle from the Centre</a>, The Mathematical Gazette, Vol. 50, No. 373 (1966), pp. 283-286. See p. 285.
%H A395953 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A395953 Equals 16/(15*Pi).
%F A395953 Equals binomial(2, -1/2).
%e A395953 0.3395305452627100496402853618613639723401805775796404...
%t A395953 RealDigits[16/(15*Pi), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395953 (PARI) 16/(15*Pi)
%Y A395953 Cf. A000796, A093070, A132706, A395267, A395954 (median), A395955, A395956.
